{{Han compound|辵|睘|c1=s|c2=p|t1=walk|ls=psc}} – to go back; to return.

===Etymology===
; “to return”
: From {{der|zh|aav}}; compare {{cog|km|រង្វាន់||reward; award; bonus}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Probably related to {{och-l|環|gloss=ring; to encircle}} ([[ibid]].).
; "still; also"
: The Mandarin reading ''hái'' is perhaps from ''huán'' (''huán'' → ''hán'' → ''hái''), ultimately from the verb sense "to return" ({{zh-ref|Zhao, 2018}}).
{{rfe|zh|Is the Mandarin reading of hai2 the result of repurposing an existing character? It doesn't seem to be related to non-Mandarin readings and the Old/Middle Chinese data.}}

